                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1385" type="given" value="JOSEFH"></interp>JOSEFH GORDON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am carman to Mr. Thomas Wilshire Gurney. On the 4th of April I saw the prisoner come into my master's shop, in the Edg<lb></lb>ware-road—he rolled a firkin of white lead away from the door against two</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184404080213"></xptr>
               <p>large gates in the road, and sat upon it—I went for a policeman, and when I came back he was gone—I looked round and saw him at the corner of Bell-street, rolling the firkin along the pavement—it was my master's firkin of lead.</p>
               <p>
